-- Polymetal’s Billionaire Owners Acquire Telecom Operator in Peru
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2011-12-15T10:09:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-15/polymetal-s-billionaire-owners-acquire-telecom-operator-in-peru.html
Polymetal International Plc ’s
billionaire shareholders Alexander Nesis and  Alexander Mamut 
acquired a Peruvian broadband internet service provider.  Mamut’s investment vehicle A&NN and the Nesis-led ICT Group
acquired 88 percent of Lima-based Yota Del  Peru , Igor Litvak,
director of investments at ICT, said by phone from Moscow today.  The new owners will invest more than $100 million to obtain
300,000 subscribers by 2015, according to an e-mailed statement
that didn’t disclose the deal’s terms. ICT Group owns broadband
internet providers in Italy and Bangladesh, Litvak said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
